itment of c billion of financial assistance from the federal and provincial governments amid declining sales contents  history  mclaughlin and buick  chevrolet   canadian auto workers bargaining  canadian factories  former plants  models currently made in canada  former models made in canada  former marques exclusive to canada  see also  references  external links historyedit mclaughlin and buickedit mclaughlin motor car company was founded in  samuel mclaughlin and william c durant respectively the biggest carriage builders in canada and the united states contracted for durants buick to supply mclaughlin with power trains for  years mclaughlin fitted the power trains to running gear bodies and chassis built by mclaughlin in canada the cars were branded mclaughlin until the end of the contract mclaughlinbuick was the brand between  and  in  durant and mclaughlin started general motors holding company after durant exchanged  of buick stock for  of mclaughlin motor co stock mclaughlin also exchanged his buick stock for general motors stock and in  was invited to be on the board of general motors in detroit chevroletedit in  mclaughlin acquired the chevrolet car company of canada which built chevrolets in oshawa with chevrolet motors and mclaughlin bodies in  he merged his company with it under the name general motors of canada limited prior to his becoming director and vice president of general motors on the approval of durant who was then president of general motors and owner of the chevrolet motor co the corporation moved people in  after mclaughlin allied his company with the corporation unknown to robert mclaughlinmclaughlinbuickcanadas standard car virtualmuseumca  the mclaughlins were given gm stocks for the propriortorship of the canadian company and  to build walkerville and canadian products as september   financial post page  reported but not ownership a chevrolet maple leaf truck built in oshawa and sold in canada with minor trim differences to the american trucks  mclaughlin buick rhd series  model  nec motor show birmingham uk gm canada is a private subsidiary that is wholly allied noted by the canadian motor tractor and implement journal  by general motors so information such as assets revenues and profits are not disclosed nonetheless gm canada has historically been one of the largest and most powerful corporations in canada being listed as the third largest in  and being comparable to several publicly traded companies such as bce george weston limited and royal bank of canada general motors of canada opened its new head office building on the shore of lake ontario in  it is a fixture on highway  and usually displays an enormous picture of a new vehicle on its huge glass atrium this is a rented structure of general motors corporation and today is called general motors general motors of canada built their first offices on richmond street in oshawa and had large general motors of canada signage from  the mclaughlin plants were there and were resigned by the mclaughlin family gms canadian regional engineering centre opened in june  it is primarily responsible for managing the design and validation of vehicles which are manufactured in canada though it supports many joint development efforts with gm operations in other countries the manufacturing plants located in oshawa produced the chevrolet from  and today the camaro and included the chevrolet truck company of canada  cadillac and lasalle were built here too the oshawa plants have regularly garnered top quality ratings by jd power the oshawa facility was ranked number  facility in overall quality in north and south america by jd power and associatescitation needed the truck plant was closed to give industry to mexicoand reopen old saturn plants general motors of canada announced a naming rights deal for the general motors centre in oshawa on october   the centres main tenants are the oshawa generals junior hockey team who were named for the company in  on april   gm canada announced that it would cut over half of its canadian jobs and close  of its canadian dealerships by  in response to its parent companys dire financial straits reducing its franchises in canada from approximately  dealerships to   across the country after general motors us bankruptcy the canadian government sold its  of general motors stock purchased in  in early   canadian auto workers bargainingedit this section needs expansion you can help by adding to it june  general motors and the canadian auto workers union reached a tentative agreement on a new collective bargaining contract on may   a full four months before the existing contract was due to expire as part of the agreement gm pledged to maintain production at the oshawa ontario pickup truck plant and made other production commitments on june   less than three weeks after ratification of the new contract gm announced that due to soaring gasoline prices and plummeting truck sales it would close four additional truck and suv plants including the oshawa pickup plant in response the caw organized a blockade of the gm of canada headquarters in oshawa the blockade was ended by an ontario superior court order after  days further discussions between gm and the caw resulted in an agreement to compensate workers at the truck plant and additional product commitments for the oshawa car assembly plant canadian factoriesedit plant location year opened products made cami automotive  ingersoll street ingersoll ontario  chevrolet equinox gmc terrain oshawa car assembly moving to the south plant started in   park road south oshawa ontario  cadillac xts chevrolet impala st catharines enginetransmission  glendale avenue st catharines ontario  former plantsedit scarborough van assembly  regina car plant   federally owned regina industries ltd until  saintethérèse quebec  windsor transmission plant  oshawa truck plant  gm north plant oshawa  models currently made in canadaedit a vancouver  winter olympics vehicle in vancouver gm canada was a sponsor of the vancouver  olympics chevrolet equinox ingersoll cami automotive  oshawa car gmc terrain ingersoll cami automotive cadillac xts oshawa car chevrolet colorado ingersoll cami automotive chevrolet trailblazer ingersoll cami automotive gmc canyon ingersoll cami automotive former models made in canadaedit buick regal oshawa car chevrolet impala oshawa car chevrolet camaro oshawa car chevrolet camaro saintethérèse quebec car pontiac trans am saintethérèse quebec car chevrolet silverado oshawa truck gmc sierra oshawa truck isuzu ascender ingersoll cami automotive chevrolet blazergmc jimmy ingersoll cami automotive former marques exclusive to canadaedit acadian  to   canadianbuilt chevrolet iis asüna   rebadged imported isuzu suzuki and daewoo models beaumont  to   based on chevrolet chevelle envoy – rebadged imported britishbuilt vauxhall and bedford models passport   rebadged imported isuzu saab and daewoo models see alsoedit general motors oshawa  detailed history of the early years of gm in canada samuel mclaughlin  the first president of gm canada final offer  documentary film that shows the  contract negotiations foreign ownership of companies of canada canadian military pattern truck  an important part of gm canadas contribution to the war effort in world war ii oshawa generals and general motors centre referencesedit gmc to add minivan gm to discontinue others jd power website  httpwwwgmcainmgmcanadaenglishaboutoverviewoverviewhtml  industry canada  the governments of canada and ontario reject automakers restructuring plans retrieved    history of gm canada gmca retrieved    the top   canadas largest companies c  business archived february   at the wayback machine  jd power and associates jdpowercom  retrieved    gm to drop pontiac in  cut thousands more jobs cbc news april      archived december   at the wayback machine  this page is available to globeplus subscribers theglobeandmailcom retrieved   external linksedit gm canada web